---
description: Project workflow and implementation discipline
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Preserve the working monolith as the source of truth until the modular path is fully wired.
- Do not rewrite large sections of code unless explicitly asked.
- Prefer extracting existing logic over inventing new architecture.
- Before coding, state the exact files to change and why.
- After coding, summarize behavior-preserving refactor changes separately from behavior changes.
- For non-trivial changes, propose the smallest verification step.
- Do not silently change file naming, ordering, or output format behavior.